result.name: Brecht's Circle

reviews.text: Amazing Nagronis. Smoking out front, and reasonable prices. Just a few feet from Times Square hustle and bustle, but feels like a world apart. Enjoy!
I worked here in the summer of 1995 and it is still one of my favourites bars in all the world. Great to see it is still going, hi Freddie...

What a great find! Excellent little bar with very reasonable prices for HK Island. The girls on staff were very friendly and attentive.

The whiskey and cocktail selection is very comprehensive, we were very impressed.

The decor is modern and chic as well as being clean and tidy. We're in Hong Kong for two more weeks on business and I'm sure to be returning before we fly out. 

Many thanks for this evening, see you soon.

Not many funky little places to grab a reasonably priced pint and good bar food in Causeway Bay. Glad I was shown this one by a friend. 
Some good whiskeys too if that's your thing.
Cute ex-pat bar 👌

I worked here in the summer of 1995 and it is still one of my favourites bars in all the world. Great to see it is still going, hi Freddie...
